title.narrative: Improved use of climate data in economic planning and disaster risk mitigation through Kenya Meteorological Department (KMD)

Number of end-users reached with relevant downscaled climate data and information to support decisions making for their operations.
Disaggregated by type and gender of end-user.
(milestone target)

Green growth and sustainable environment and natural resource management mainstreamed by counties through the County Integrated Development Plans (CIDPs) and other county plans (# sustainable natural resource management plan)

One pilot multi-county integrated sustainable natural resources management (NRM) plan for one Water Tower developed, and policy-related learning documented to inform the Water Tower Policy.
Measured as % of roadmap complete.
(new indicator. No indicator in the DED Results Framework)
Green Growth and sustainable environment and natural resource management mainstreamed by counties through County interated Development Plans (CIDPs) and other County Plans (reformulated)

No. of county level projects informed by national level policies.
The indicator has been reformulated to assess the work that MEF will do to mainstream national policies into the 8 counties selected by NEMA as their "deep dive" (pilot) counties.
Improved public policy environment for the private sector engagement in green growth and sustainable environment and natural resource management

No. of green growth policy-related decisions published (such as tax exemptions on green products, energy efficiency use, media coverage on green growth, and use/manufacture of environmental friendly products. )
Improved use of climate data in economic planning and disaster risk mitigation (through Kenya Meteorological Department (KMD))

No. and type of end-users such as small scale farmers and health policy planners applying climate data and information in their operations
(This indicator and targets were reformulated to reflect the work of Kenya Meteorological Department (KMD) of the MEF to downscale climate data and information to users in counties.)
Green procurement of goods and services undertaken by public entities (through an engagement with the Public Procurement and Oversight Authority-PPOA-2 Green Procurement Circulars produced

Green public procurement (GPP) framework, regulations and circulars in place and green procurement by public entities started. Measured as % of roadmap / milestones to GGP: engagement with PPRA, GPP framework in place, circulars and agreements in place, GPP started by 50 public entities.
("Public Entity" means MDA or County. )
Enhanced enabling environment for green growth and sustainable natural resource management (performance index)

Improved Environmental Performance Index (EPI).
EPI is an environmental performance or quality measure that tracks how well a country performs on environmental management against two overriding issues or objectives: Environmental Health (measures the protection of human health from environmental harm) and Ecosystem Vitality (measures ecosystem protection and resource management)
Enhanced enabling environment for green growth and sustainable natural resource management (#2 green growth and green economy mainstreamed)

The extent to which Green Growth (GG) and the Green Economy (GE) are mainstreamed into MEF and government policy development and implementation.
(Assessed through a scorecard with milestone criteria 0 to 100%).
